Here’s what changed:

1. Removed uncertainty everywhere
TechnicalSignal, /api/signal/[symbol] (RealSignal), StockSignal, and signal-engine no longer define or return it.
UI: dropped uncertainty labels; chart strip now says confidence comes from weighted indicator agreement.
Reliability score (demo + live panels) is now
min(100, round(confidence × 0.65 + |bullStrength − bearStrength| × 0.35)).
Secondary header stat is bull/bear skew (|bull − bear| from the same vote engine).
2. Extended indicators now vote
In scoreTechnicals, these are added to the same BUY/SELL/HOLD vote list (with weights):

RS(252d) — 1.8
Alpha(63d) — 1.5
Beta(ATR) — 1.0 (high vol → slight SELL lean; low vol → slight BUY)
Gamma(RSIΔ) — 1.2
Theta(trend) — 1.3 (persistent trend vs EMA20)
Stoch %K — 1.5
Williams %R — 1.5
Existing voters (RSI, MACD, EMA20/50, price/EMA20, ROC) and the volume boost are unchanged.

3. Confidence is deterministic
No randomness. After volume scaling:

BUY: margin = (buyScore − sellScore) / (buyScore + sellScore)
SELL: margin = (sellScore − buyScore) / total
HOLD: margin = 1 − 2 × min(buy,sell) / total (larger when buy/sell are close)
Then:

confidence = round(50 + 45 × clamp(margin, 0, 1)), clamped to 50–95.

So confidence rises when the weighted vote margin is large and sits near 50 when the model is conflicted (especially on HOLD).

indicatorVotes in the API now includes all of the above labels, so the overlay “Drivers” list matches what drives direction and confidence.